* an enum type is one with its values enumerated with names in the definition
* to introduce the syntax, here are some examples
	* datatype Color = green | blue | red
	* datatype Bool = false | true
* the number of cases may be 1
	* datatype Singleton = single
	* though in practice: more often the 0-tuple is used as a singleton type, becaue that one is part of the language
* the number of cases may be 0
	* datatype Void =
	* exactly 0 value exists with type Void
	* the usual names for an empty type are "Void", "Empty", "Absurd"
